            "id": "4574357",
            "title": "Goldman Sachs GAAP EPS of $17.55 beats by $1.16, revenue of $17.23B beats by $300M",
            "description": "<html><body><ul>\n<li>Goldman Sachs <a href=\"https://www.goldmansachs.com/pressroom/press-releases/current/pdfs/2026-q1-results.pdf\" rel=\"nofollow\">press release</a> (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/GS\" title=\"The Goldman Sachs Group, Inc.\">GS</a></span>): Q1 GAAP EPS of $17.55 <span> beats by $1.16</span>.</li>\n<li>Revenue of $17.23B (+14.4% Y/Y) <span> beats by $300M</span>.</li>\n<li>Net revenues were $17.23 billion for the first quarter of 2026, 14% higher than thefirst quarter of 2025 and 28% higher than the fourth quarter of 2025. The increasecompared with the first quarter of 2025 primarily reflected higher net revenues inGlobal Banking &amp; Markets.</li>\n<li>Annualized return on average common shareholders' equity (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/ROE\" title=\"Astoria US Equal Weight Quality Kings ETF\">ROE</a>) was 19.8% for the first quarter of 2026.</li>\n<li>Book value per common share increased by 1.0% during the quarter to $361.19.</li>\n<li> </li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"signup_widget_placeholder\"></div>\n</body></html>",
            "image": "https://static.seekingalpha.com/assets/og_image_1200-29b2bfe1a595477db6826bd2126c63ac2091efb7ec76347a8e7f81ba17e3de6c.png",
            "link": "https://seekingalpha.com/news/4574357-goldman-sachs-gaap-eps-of-17_55-beats-by-1_16-revenue-of-17_23b-beats-by-300m",
            "pub_date": "2026-04-13 19:31:51",
            "source": "seekalpha",
            "kind": 1,
            "language": "en"
