            "id": "4574346",
            "title": "Holcim’s Lafarge reportedly found guilty over Syria terrorist payments",
            "description": "<html><body><ul>\n<li class=\"ArticleBodyText_articleBodyContent__17wqE typography_articleBody___5jDr\" data-component=\"paragraph\">Cement ‌maker Holcim Ltd.’s (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/HCMLF\" title=\"Holcim AG\">HCMLF</a></span>) Lafarge unit was found guilty by a Paris court of making payments to terrorist organizations to keep open a plant during the civil war in Syria, according to multiple media reports on Monday.</li>\n<li class=\"ArticleBodyText_articleBodyContent__17wqE typography_articleBody___5jDr\" data-component=\"paragraph\">The court convicted Lafarge for violating European sanctions and terrorism financing. The company’s former chief executive officer Bruno Lafont was also found guilty. Sentencing is expected later on Monday, as per reports.</li>\n<li class=\"ArticleBodyText_articleBodyContent__17wqE typography_articleBody___5jDr\" data-component=\"paragraph\">The French firm earlier pleaded guilty in the United States to providing material support to terrorists and paid a $778 million fine.</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"signup_widget_placeholder\"></div>\n</body></html>",
            "image": "https://static.seekingalpha.com/assets/og_image_1200-29b2bfe1a595477db6826bd2126c63ac2091efb7ec76347a8e7f81ba17e3de6c.png",
