            "id": "4574269",
            "title": "Cathie Wood's ARK boosts Palantir, Tesla, Roninhood bets; cuts semiconductor exposure",
            "description": "<html><body><p data-eci=\"true\">Cathie Wood’s ARK Invest funds executed a broad rotation across technology, healthcare, and industrial names during the last week while markets remained volatile over broader geopolitical tensions between the U.S. and Iran.</p>\n<p>Buying activity for the portfolio manager was led by Palantir Technologies (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/PLTR\" title=\"Palantir Technologies Inc.\">PLTR</a>), Tesla (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/TSLA\" title=\"Tesla, Inc.\">TSLA</a>), and Robinhood Markets (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/HOOD\" title=\"Robinhood Markets, Inc.\">HOOD</a>), while the largest sales came from Strata Critical Medical (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/SRTA\" title=\"Strata Critical Medical, Inc.\">SRTA</a>), Teradyne (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/TER\" title=\"Teradyne, Inc.\">TER</a>), Advanced Micro Devices (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/AMD\" title=\"Advanced Micro Devices, Inc.\">AMD</a>), and BWX Technologies (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/BWXT\" title=\"BWX Technologies, Inc.\">BWXT</a>).</p>\n<p>Digging deeper into sector-wise moves, Ark increased exposure to AI and data analytics platforms. Palantir Technologies (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/PLTR\" title=\"Palantir Technologies Inc.\">PLTR</a>) led inflows with 85K shares bought across ARKF (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/ARKF\" title=\"ARK Blockchain &amp; Fintech Innovation ETF\">ARKF</a></span>), ARKK (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/ARKK\" title=\"ARK Innovation ETF\">ARKK</a></span>), ARKQ (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/ARKQ\" title=\"ARK Autonomous Technology &amp; Robotics ETF\">ARKQ</a></span>), ARKW (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/ARKW\" title=\"ARK Next Generation Internet ETF\">ARKW</a></span>), and ARKX (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/ARKX\" title=\"ARK Space &amp; Defense Innovation ETF\">ARKX</a></span>), for an estimated trade value of $11M. In autonomous technology, Kodiak AI (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/KDK\" title=\"Kodiak AI, Inc.\">KDK</a>) saw 31,291 shares accumulated exclusively in ARKQ (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/ARKQ\" title=\"ARK Autonomous Technology &amp; Robotics ETF\">ARKQ</a>).</p>\n<p>Moving to electric vehicles and mobility, Tesla (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/TSLA\" title=\"Tesla, Inc.\">TSLA</a>) remained a core conviction buy, with over 79K shares added across ARKK (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/ARKK\" title=\"ARK Innovation ETF\">ARKK</a>), ARKQ (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/ARKQ\" title=\"ARK Autonomous Technology &amp; Robotics ETF\">ARKQ</a>), and ARKX (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/ARKX\" title=\"ARK Space &amp; Defense Innovation ETF\">ARKX</a>), <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/news/4573611-cathie-wood-buys-the-dip-in-tesla-with-fresh-28m-investment\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"increasing exposure by $28M\">increasing exposure by $28M</a>. <span class=\"whitespace-normal\">Cathie Wood</span><span> has consistently underscored autonomous driving as the cornerstone of ARK’s long-term thesis on </span><span class=\"whitespace-normal\">Tesla (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/TSLA\" title=\"Tesla, Inc.\">TSLA</a>) and currently has over $880M worth of exposure to the stock.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"whitespace-normal\">In fintech &amp; digital platforms, the portfolio manager added over 182K shares of Robinhood Markets (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/HOOD\" title=\"Robinhood Markets, Inc.\">HOOD</a>) across ARKF (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/ARKF\" title=\"ARK Blockchain &amp; Fintech Innovation ETF\">ARKF</a>), ARKK (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/ARKK\" title=\"ARK Innovation ETF\">ARKK</a>), and ARKW (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/ARKW\" title=\"ARK Next Generation Internet ETF\">ARKW</a>), with an estimated value close to $12.7M. In contrast, Intercontinental Exchange (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/ICE\" title=\"Intercontinental Exchange, Inc.\">ICE</a>) saw 6.9K shares worth ~$1.2M being sold from ARKF (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/ARKF\" title=\"ARK Blockchain &amp; Fintech Innovation ETF\">ARKF</a>), indicating a shift away from traditional exchange infrastructure toward next-generation fintech platforms. Besides, LY Corp (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/YAHOF\" title=\"LY Corporation\">YAHOF</a>) (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/YAHOY\" title=\"LY Corporation\">YAHOY</a>), a Japanese internet conglomerate, also saw 9.8K shares sold, reflecting trimming of international platform exposure.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"whitespace-normal\">Genomics &amp; healthcare strategies showed selective buying, with ~49K shares of GeneDx (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/WGS\" title=\"GeneDx Holdings Corp.\">WGS</a>) bought and 8.2K shares of Arcturus Therapeutics (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/ARCT\" title=\"Arcturus Therapeutics Holdings Inc.\">ARCT</a>) added. On the sell side, Twist Bioscience (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/TWST\" title=\"Twist Bioscience Corporation\">TWST</a>) saw a disposal of 60K shares, while most notably, Strata Critical Medical (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/SRTA\" title=\"Strata Critical Medical, Inc.\">SRTA</a>) witnessed a massive 355K share sell-off. G<span>enomic diagnostics company Veracyte (</span>VCYT) also made it to the sell list.</span><span class=\"whitespace-normal\"></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"whitespace-normal\">The firm remained a net seller in semiconductors &amp; automation; it dropped over 44K shares of Advanced Micro Devices (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/AMD\" title=\"Advanced Micro Devices, Inc.\">AMD</a>), reversing the buy trend seen in February. Semiconductor test equipment maker Teradyne (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/TER\" title=\"Teradyne, Inc.\">TER</a>) saw over 68K shares dropped across ARKK (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/ARKK\" title=\"ARK Innovation ETF\">ARKK</a>) and ARKQ (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/ARKQ\" title=\"ARK Autonomous Technology &amp; Robotics ETF\">ARKQ</a>) worth close to $11M, maintaining the selling spree over the last few months.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"whitespace-normal\"><span class=\"whitespace-normal\">Over 36K shares of BWX Technologies (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/BWXT\" title=\"BWX Technologies, Inc.\">BWXT</a>)<span>—</span>a nuclear technology and defense-focused industrial company—were sold across ARKK (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/ARKK\" title=\"ARK Innovation ETF\">ARKK</a>) and ARKQ (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/ARKQ\" title=\"ARK Autonomous Technology &amp; Robotics ETF\">ARKQ</a>). </span></span>Other sell trades include uranium producer Cameco (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/CCJ\" title=\"Cameco Corporation\">CCJ</a>) and streaming platform company Roku (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/ROKU\" title=\"Roku, Inc.\">ROKU</a>).</p>\n<div class=\"signup_widget_placeholder\"></div>\n</body></html>",
